Introduction:
rklogger is a command line program for reading the parameters out of
Danfoss inverters. This project is licensed under the GPLv3. It is testet with
TLX and ULX inverters.


Build:
Recent versions of cmake, gnumake and g++ are required.

Please type within the project root directory:

cmake .
make

to build the project.



Usage:

To read a parameter:
./rklogger <network> <node> <param_idx> <param_subidx> <param_modulidx>

To ping a inverter:
./rklogger <network> <node>

For details regarding param_idx, param_subidx and param_modulidx please refer to the ComLynx
protocol specification provided by Danfoss.
